  <!-- Cost Factor -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section__header">
      <div class="section__number">Section 6.3</div>
      <h2 class="section__title">Cost Factor (Salt Rounds)</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="section__content">
      <p>The cost factor determines how many iterations the hashing algorithm runs. Each increment <strong>doubles</strong> the computation time. This is the key mechanism that makes bcrypt resistant to brute-force attacks over time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Cost Factor</th>
            <th>Iterations</th>
            <th>Hash Time (approx)</th>
            <th>Use Case</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>8</code></td>
            <td>256</td>
            <td>~40ms</td>
            <td>⚠️ Too fast for production</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>10</code></td>
            <td>1,024</td>
            <td>~100ms</td>
            <td>Minimum recommended</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>12</code></td>
            <td>4,096</td>
            <td>~300ms</td>
            <td>✅ Good balance (recommended default)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>14</code></td>
            <td>16,384</td>
            <td>~1 sec</td>
            <td>✅ High security</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>16</code></td>
            <td>65,536</td>
            <td>~4 sec</td>
            <td>Very high security (may affect UX)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>20</code></td>
            <td>1,048,576</td>
            <td>~60 sec</td>
            <td>❌ Too slow for real-time auth</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box info-box--remediation">
      <div class="info-box__title">✅ How to Choose the Right Cost Factor</div>
      <div class="info-box__content">
        <ul>
          <li>Benchmark on your production hardware: target <strong>250ms–1 second</strong> per hash</li>
          <li>Start at <strong>cost 12</strong> and increase every ~2 years as hardware improves</li>
          <li>Remember: users only hash during login/registration (low frequency)</li>
          <li>On hash: measure time → if &lt; 250ms → increase cost factor</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Hashing vs Encryption -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section__header">
      <div class="section__number">Section 6.4</div>
      <h2 class="section__title">Hashing vs Encryption vs Encoding</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>Hashing (bcrypt)</th><th>Encryption (AES)</th><th>Encoding (Base64)</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Reversible?</strong></td>
            <td>❌ One-way (irreversible)</td>
            <td>✅ Two-way (decrypt with key)</td>
            <td>✅ Two-way (trivially decodes)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Purpose</strong></td>
            <td>Password storage, integrity</td>
            <td>Protecting sensitive data</td>
            <td>Data transport (not security!)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Key required?</strong></td>
            <td>No key. Uses salt (stored in hash)</td>
            <td>Yes. Encryption key required</td>
            <td>No key. Public algorithm</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Same input → same output?</strong></td>
            <td>No! (different salt each time)</td>
            <td>Depends on mode (ECB yes, CBC/GCM no)</td>
            <td>Yes — always deterministic</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Security</strong></td>
            <td>Can't get password back</td>
            <td>Data protected while at rest</td>
            <td>❌ NOT security — just encoding!</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Example</strong></td>
            <td>bcrypt, Argon2, scrypt</td>
            <td>AES-256-GCM, ChaCha20</td>
            <td>Base64, URL encoding, Hex</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

